BOWIE: So, like,
you've got your grid.

15:15.102 --> 15:17.602
And then,
so, you'd have, like, tiles

15:17.702 --> 15:19.242
with all the subjects
you're into.

15:19.342 --> 15:22.062
-So, like, footy, movies...
-Radiohead.

15:23.062 --> 15:25.962
And it would be great
if you could have a...

15:26.062 --> 15:28.002
..a thing on there where
you could message each other.

15:28.102 --> 15:29.843
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Of course, of course.

15:29.943 --> 15:31.683
Oh, and! And! How's this?

15:31.783 --> 15:33.283
When you connect with someone,

15:33.383 --> 15:35.803
you have this little animation
that pops up

15:35.903 --> 15:38.463
which has, like, two beers
clinking together.

15:39.463 --> 15:41.603
-Maybe.
-What?

15:41.703 --> 15:43.743
You don't think
it's a stupid idea?

15:44.743 --> 15:46.523
What, a phone app?

15:46.623 --> 15:48.804
Does the world really need
another app?

15:48.904 --> 15:49.804
(COCKATIEL SQUAWKS)

15:49.904 --> 15:51.764
Turtle reckons it's a good idea.

15:51.864 --> 15:53.884
-Oh, love ya, Turts.
-Yeah, see?

15:53.984 --> 15:56.924
So, like, this is exactly what
you were talking about, Dad,

15:57.024 --> 16:00.084
like, you know, about being,
like, lonely for male company.

16:00.184 --> 16:01.484
Male mental health,
it's a thing.

16:01.584 --> 16:03.644
And there's an app
for everything else.

16:03.744 --> 16:07.565
You know, why not one for
old guys meeting new friends?

16:07.665 --> 16:09.045
Old guys?

16:09.145 --> 16:12.085
It's an app for middle-aged men

16:12.185 --> 16:13.565
who hate other people.

16:13.665 --> 16:15.045
Guys like you. Exactly.

16:15.145 --> 16:18.045
So, you know, maybe that bloke
from the movies, he'll join,

16:18.145 --> 16:19.845
and you'll find him...
find him that way.

16:19.945 --> 16:21.085
-That would be good.
-Yeah.

16:21.185 --> 16:24.446
Dad, this plays to
our strengths, you know?

16:24.546 --> 16:26.546
Thanks, mate.

16:29.826 --> 16:31.926
I just remembered. (SIGHS)

16:32.026 --> 16:35.426
I haven't thought about Katerina
in, like...

16:36.586 --> 16:38.586
..20 minutes.

16:41.307 --> 16:43.967
Hey. Hey!

16:44.067 --> 16:46.587
It's like Pop always said.

16:47.587 --> 16:50.207
Takes a lot to laugh and a...

16:50.307 --> 16:51.407
Say it with me.

16:51.507 --> 16:53.767
BOTH: ..a train to cry.

16:53.867 --> 16:55.867
(TURTLE CHIRPS)

16:58.108 --> 17:00.108
What does that mean?

17:01.148 --> 17:02.248
(ADJUSTS RADIO DIAL)

17:02.348 --> 17:03.608
Oi.

17:03.708 --> 17:05.908
(WOMAN SPEAKS IN SPANISH
ON RADIO)

17:09.388 --> 17:11.388
Who bought me shampoo?

17:18.669 --> 17:19.609
Goodnight!

17:19.709 --> 17:21.709
Goodnight.

17:23.869 --> 17:24.609
(WOMAN CONTINUES SPEAKING
SPANISH ON RADIO)

17:31.309 --> 17:33.310
(CRICKETS CHIRP)

17:35.470 --> 17:37.470
You sleeping here tonight?

17:39.590 --> 17:41.590
Still in the van?

17:42.870 --> 17:44.870
You deserve to be.

17:48.110 --> 17:50.110
(MATIAS SIGHS)

17:53.551 --> 17:55.551
(SIGHS)

18:03.351 --> 18:06.071
(SULTRY MUSIC)

18:11.272 --> 18:13.272
(VIBRATOR BUZZES)

18:26.193 --> 18:28.193
(BABY CRIES)

18:32.073 --> 18:34.073
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

18:36.993 --> 18:39.253
Oly! What are you doing?

18:39.353 --> 18:41.213
Mum! No, no, no, no, no!

18:41.313 --> 18:44.054
Oh, Mum! I was trying
to let her self-settle.

18:44.154 --> 18:46.294
What? You're
controlled-crying her?

18:46.394 --> 18:48.494
Is Santi involved with that?
That's a really big decision!

18:48.594 --> 18:50.094
Well, I don't know
what else to do!

18:50.194 --> 18:52.654
You go to sleep.
I'll settle her.

18:52.754 --> 18:54.174
Are you sure?

18:54.274 --> 18:56.094
Yes! Shh-shh.

18:56.194 --> 18:58.054
You've got Migaloo.
It's all right.

18:58.154 --> 18:59.694
-Um...
-What are you doing?

18:59.794 --> 19:02.495
Just go to bed. We'll be fine.

19:02.595 --> 19:04.535
She can't have Migaloo.
He's mine.

19:04.635 --> 19:06.295
-(CONTINUES CRYING)
-Shh.

19:06.395 --> 19:08.175
Hey!

19:08.275 --> 19:11.535
Grandma's gonna get you
another toy.

19:11.635 --> 19:13.375
But not Migaloo!

19:13.475 --> 19:15.015
Goodnight.

19:15.115 --> 19:17.115
(CONTINUES CRYING)

19:19.396 --> 19:21.416
Look, let's go outside!

19:21.516 --> 19:25.696
What do we think? It's
a beautiful night out here.

19:25.796 --> 19:27.656
What do you think? Look.
(GASPS)

19:27.756 --> 19:29.656
Oh, is that a car?
(GASPS)

19:29.756 --> 19:31.696
Look at the car going past.

19:31.796 --> 19:33.456
(SCREAMS)

19:33.556 --> 19:36.837
Oh, please stop crying.

19:38.037 --> 19:39.897
Please stop crying.

19:39.997 --> 19:42.037
(BABY GRIZZLES)

19:51.117 --> 19:53.118
(FALLS SILENT)

20:00.358 --> 20:01.578
(WHISPERS) She's asleep?

20:01.678 --> 20:03.958
(WHISPERS) Yes. Shh, shh, shh.

20:06.278 --> 20:09.778
Oh, no! Mum, she's pooed!

20:09.878 --> 20:11.819
It's fine.
Let's just put her down.

20:11.919 --> 20:14.619
No, she's gonna get a rash.
It's gonna be ten times worse.

20:14.719 --> 20:16.579
-Mum...
-Please.

20:16.679 --> 20:19.059
I can change her
without waking her.

20:19.159 --> 20:21.719
-Please, no.
-Mum, Mum, Mum...

20:22.799 --> 20:24.799
I can do it.

20:50.401 --> 20:53.721
(VELCRO RIPS)

20:56.921 --> 20:59.401
(VELCRO RIPS)

21:03.802 --> 21:05.382
(BABY CRIES)

21:05.482 --> 21:07.642
(WHISPERS) Oh, my God.

21:20.522 --> 21:21.583
-(CONTINUES CRYING)
-OK.

21:21.683 --> 21:23.143
OK, OK, come on. Enough.

21:23.243 --> 21:25.243
Enough.

21:31.723 --> 21:33.263
-(SOUND EFFECTS ON TV)
-Mum!

21:33.363 --> 21:36.623
We are not using screens
as a pacifier. (SWITCHES TV OFF)

21:36.723 --> 21:39.244
(BABY WAILS)

21:43.844 --> 21:45.184
Mum!

21:45.284 --> 21:46.664
(CHATTER ON TV)

21:46.764 --> 21:47.984
(GURGLES SOFTLY)

21:48.084 --> 21:50.904
-What are you drawing?
-Jet pack cat!

21:51.004 --> 21:52.984
Do you know how
irresponsible it is

21:53.084 --> 21:55.945
to condition a child to only
settle in front of a screen?

21:56.045 --> 21:58.185
The kind of hardwiring

21:58.285 --> 22:00.665
that's laying down
in the brain forever?

22:00.765 --> 22:03.465
I'm gonna send you the research.

22:03.565 --> 22:05.725
I'm sorry, Oly, but...

22:07.085 --> 22:10.465
..the only way I used to settle
you was in front of a screen.

22:10.565 --> 22:12.565
Such a bad parent.

22:14.246 --> 22:16.246
(SIGHS)

22:18.486 --> 22:20.486
I know.

22:24.366 --> 22:27.686
(GENTLE MUSIC)

22:57.448 --> 22:59.448
(MATIAS URINATES)

23:14.129 --> 23:16.329
(KETTLE WHISTLES)

23:18.169 --> 23:19.349
(WHISTLING STOPS)

23:19.449 --> 23:21.709
(TOASTER POPS)

23:21.809 --> 23:24.250
Hey, boys. Boys. Gabriel.

23:25.370 --> 23:27.790
You know how Papa has been
sleeping outside in the truck

23:27.890 --> 23:30.030
to stop that possum
from stealing our empanadas?

23:30.130 --> 23:31.790
He nearly caught him
the other night.

23:31.890 --> 23:32.790
ROSA: Yes, he did!

23:32.890 --> 23:34.990
So the possum has gone away

23:35.090 --> 23:37.230
to steal Mrs Nikaki's oranges
instead.

23:37.330 --> 23:38.430
Papa won.

23:38.530 --> 23:40.630
So now you can come
and kiss him tomorrow

23:40.730 --> 23:42.431
in our bed, OK?

23:42.531 --> 23:44.191
And start peeing
in the toilet again.

23:44.291 --> 23:46.411
OK. Go and wash your hands.

23:51.651 --> 23:53.551
Just like that.

23:53.651 --> 23:55.651
(SIGHS)

23:58.171 --> 23:59.672
Where are you going?

23:59.772 --> 24:03.352
Um...to Oly's house.

24:03.452 --> 24:05.112
To see my daughter.

24:05.212 --> 24:07.212
Let me drive you.

24:13.172 --> 24:15.172
(CAR PULLS UP OUTSIDE)

24:21.413 --> 24:23.413
(CAR DOORS CLOSE)

24:23.933 --> 24:25.933
Why are you so angry?

24:26.453 --> 24:28.693
-Because of Rosa and I?
-No.

24:30.893 --> 24:33.213
-No, Dad.
-What, then?

24:37.054 --> 24:38.994
Remember my seventh birthday,
Dad?

24:39.094 --> 24:41.234
'Course you don't.

24:41.334 --> 24:43.334
'Cause you weren't there.

24:43.974 --> 24:45.974
You were hungover
in bed all day.

24:46.614 --> 24:48.614
You know, I got up that morning.

24:49.734 --> 24:51.735
Made my own birthday cake.

24:52.735 --> 24:53.875
I cut a slice for Mum,

24:53.975 --> 24:55.875
'cause I had to imagine
she was there for me.

24:55.975 --> 24:58.275
Man, I had just lost my wife!

24:58.375 --> 25:00.375
I'd just lost my mum, Dad!

25:01.615 --> 25:03.615
I needed you, Dad.

25:04.695 --> 25:06.695
And the truth is
you weren't there.

25:09.616 --> 25:11.616
You've never been there.

25:13.256 --> 25:15.256
(SIGHS)

25:18.656 --> 25:20.556
(FLOORBOARDS CREAK)

25:20.656 --> 25:22.656
OLY: What are you doing?

25:33.177 --> 25:34.397
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

25:34.497 --> 25:36.497
You're in love with him.

25:37.457 --> 25:39.457
I was.

25:40.537 --> 25:42.537
I'm not.

25:43.617 --> 25:45.358
(SIGHS)

25:45.458 --> 25:46.798
It just hurts.

25:46.898 --> 25:48.898
(SNIFFLES)

25:53.778 --> 25:56.458
Santi really loved
that poem, Mum.

25:57.938 --> 25:59.938
So did I.

26:03.179 --> 26:05.859
('TODO TIENE SU FIN'
BY DOM LA NENA)

26:07.619 --> 26:09.399
(BABY GURGLES)

26:09.499 --> 26:11.939
(CHUCKLES) Hey, love.

26:15.139 --> 26:18.139
('TODO TIENE SU FIN'
BY DOM LA NENA CONTINUES)

27:20.103 --> 27:23.003
('TODO TIENE SU FIN'
BY DOM LA NENA CONTINUES)
